###Finding $\cos(\theta_1)$

Since $\theta_1$ is in Quadrant $\text{I}$, $\cos\theta_1$ is positive. 

$\begin{align}\cos(\theta_1)&=\sqrt{\cos^2(\theta_1)}
\\&=\sqrt{\dfrac{111}{400}}
\\&=\dfrac{\sqrt{111}}{20}\end{align}$

###Calculating the midline

According to the graph, the maximum value of the function is $-3.7$, and its minimum value is $-11$.

$\begin{align}\text{midline}&=\dfrac{\text{max value}+\text{min value}}{2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-3.7+(-11)}{2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-14.7}{2}
\\\\
&=-7.35
\end{align}$

###Calculating amplitude

According to the graph, the maximum value of the function is $-3.7$ and its minimum value is $-11$.

$\begin{align}\text{amplitude}&=\dfrac{\text{max value}-\text{min value}}{2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-3.7-(-11)}{2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{7.3}{2}
\\\\
&=3.65
\end{align}$
